cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a weakly supervised deep learning method for object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method uses an encoder-decoder network, which is a type of neural network commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the comparison of the proposed method with other state-of-the-art methods, which involves evaluating the performance of the models (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method is in the detection of brain lesions in 3D MRI scans, which involves medical imaging (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
